  <h1>The Eggcellent Bite</h1>

  <h2>Deviled Eggs</h2>

  <p>Recipe source: https://www.simplyrecipes.com/recipes/deviled_eggs/</p>

  <figure>
    <img src="images/deviled-eggs.jpg" alt="Plate of deviled eggs" style="height:250px;">
    <figcaption>Classic deviled eggs served chilled</figcaption>
  </figure>

  <h3>Ingredients</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>6 hard-boiled eggs</li>
    <li>3 tablespoons mayonnaise</li>
    <li>1 teaspoon mustard</li>
    <li>Salt and pepper to taste</li>
    <li>Paprika for garnish</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Equipment</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Medium saucepan</li>
    <li>Mixing bowl</li>
    <li>Fork or whisk</li>
    <li>Knife</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Directions</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Peel the eggs and slice them in half lengthwise.</li>
    <li>Remove the yolks and place them in a bowl.</li>
    <li>Mash yolks with mayonnaise, mustard, salt, and pepper.</li>
    <li>Spoon or pipe the mixture back into the egg whites.</li>
    <li>Sprinkle with paprika and chill before serving.</li>
  </ol>

